DFProperties.DFTitle: This interior node distinguishes different EAP methods.
The EAP Type [WPA] specifies the EAP method type of the actual method.
The EAP Vendor ID specifies the SMI Network Management Private Enterprise Code of the Vendor of the actual method.
The EAP Vendor Type specifies the vendor specific method type.
The UserIdentity parameter specifies the user’s identity [RFC3748].
Password is the password that is used in EAP Authentication.
The Realm parameter specifies the override realm that is sent, for example, in the EAP Identity/Response packet [RFC3748].
This leaf node exists in order to inform the device of the policy about the identity privacy.
Certain EAP methods can run other methods encapsulated in a secure tunnel.
VfyServerRealm [802.
This interior node contains a list of server realms.
This interior node distinguishes the different server realms.
The ServerRealm node defines an allowed realm that the device will accept.
For those EAP types that use certificates, the required user certificates are specified in this subtree.
This interior node distinguishes different certificates.
This node specifies the type of certificate.
SubjectKeyID specifies the subject key identifier of a certificate.
Signature specifies the digital signature of the certificate.
This interior node distinguishes different certificates.
This node specifies the type of certificate.
Signature specifies the digital signature of the certificate.
This specifies the serial number of the certificate.
Issuer is the Distinguished Name of the certificate’s issuer in human readable UTF-8 form (for example “/C=US/O=Some organization/CN=Some common name”).

This interior node specifies the unique object id of a network access point, or NAP, management object.
This leaf node defines the identity of the one specific network access point which an instance of this management object represents.
This interior node is parent node of the IP configuration sub-tree.
This optional interior node defines the IPv4 address configuration of the local terminal when this network access point is used.
If TRUE (or if this optional leaf node is absent), the terminal’s IPv4 configuration SHOULD be generated automatically.
This leaf node specifies the IPv4 address [RFC791] of the device when connected using this network access point as a string in dotted-decimal notation.
This leaf node specifies the IPv4 network address mask [RFC791] of the device when connected using this network access point as a string in dotted-decimal notation.
This optional leaf node specifies the IPv4 address [RFC791] of the Internet gateway accessible when the device is connected using this network access point as a string in dotted-decimal notation.
If TRUE (or if this optional leaf node is absent), the DNS addresses are to be configured automatically (for example using DHCP [RFC2132] protocol).
This optional interior node defines the IPv6 address configuration of the device when this network access point is used.
If TRUE (or if this optional leaf node is absent), the devices’s IPv6 configuration is generated automatically.
This leaf node specifies the IPv6 address, defined and formatted as string as specified in [RFC4291].

This leaf node specifies the IPv6 network address prefix length [RFC4291] of the device as an 7-bit unsigned integer when connected using this network access point as a string as specified in [RFC4291].
This optional leaf node specifies the IPv6 address [RFC4291] of the Internet gateway accessible when the device is connected using this network access point as a string as specified in [RFC4291].
If TRUE (or if this optional leaf node is absent), the DNS addresses are to be configured automatically (for example using following references [RFC3736] and [RFC3646].
This optional interior node defined the Mobile IP Version 4 (MIPv4) configurations [RFC3344].
This interior node defines the shared secrets used for securing the MIPv4 signaling [RFC3344].
This interior node lists all the Network Access Identifiers (NAI) [RFC4282] to be used in MIP registration.
This interior node distinguishes the Network Access Identifiers [RFC4282].
This leaf node defines the user name portion of Network Access Identifier (NAI), encoded in UTF-8 string, refer to [RFC4282].
This leaf node defines the realm portion of Network Access Identifier (NAI), encoded in UTF-8 string, refer to [RFC4282].
This leaf node defines if the user portion is pseudo generated.
This interior node defines the specific parameters for tuning the MIPv6 protocol behaviour.
This leaf node defines if reverse tunneling between a) in FA mode, the FA and the HA b) in CoA mode, the MN and the HA [RFC3024].
This leaf node defines the maximum number of registration retry attempts [RFC3344] as an 8 bit unsigned integer.
This leaf node defines the initial registration timer used in before new registration attempt as an unsigned integer.
This leaf node defines the relative re-registration period.
This leaf node defines the registration period.
This leaf node defines if Network Address Translation (NAT) traversal (UDP tunneling) is used.
This optional interior node defined the Mobile IP Version 6 (MIPv6) configurations [RFC3775].
This interior node defines the shared secrets used for securing the MIPv6 signaling [RFC3775].
This interior node lists all the Network Access Identifiers (NAI) [RFC4283] to be used in MIP registration.
This interior node distinguishes the Network Access Identifiers [RFC4283].
This leaf node defines the user name portion of Network Access Identifier (NAI), encoded in UTF-8 string, refer to [RFC4282].
This leaf node defines the realm portion of Network Access Identifier (NAI), encoded in UTF-8 string, refer to [RFC4282].

This leaf node defines the binding lifetime [RFC3775] in seconds proposed to the Home Agent in a binding update.
